12 An Act relating to schools; limiting screen time for
prekindergarten through fifth-grade public school
13 students to one hour per school day; defining term;
providing exceptions; providing for codification;
14 providing an effective date; and declaring an
emergency.
15
16
17
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 11-103.17 of Title 70, unless
22 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23 A. Beginning with the 2026-2027 school year, public school
24 students in prekindergarten through fifth grade shall be limited to
Req. No. 17146 Page 1

1 one hour of screen time per school day, inclusive of all subjects.
2 Screen time includes teacher-directed or child-selected activities
3 that utilize a computer, tablet, television, smart device,
4 Chromebook, or other similar device with an electronic display.
5 B. The screentime limitations set forth in subsection A of this
6 section shall not apply to the following:
7 1. Targeted instructional support, intervention, or
8 remediation;
9 2. Accommodations or services, including the use of assistive
10 technology, required under the Individuals with Disabilities
11 Education Act, 20 U.S.C., Section 1400 et seq., Section 504 of the
12 Rehabilitation Act of 1973, 29 U.S.C., Section 794, or the Americans
13 with Disabilities Act, 42 U.S.C., Section 12101 et seq.;
14 3. Administration of a screening instrument adopted by the
15 State Board of Education pursuant to Section 1210.508C of this
16 title, dyslexia screenings, state-adopted benchmark assessments, or
17 other assessments required by state or federal law;
18 4. Teacher preparation, lesson planning, and professional use;
19 5. Computer programming classes; and
20 6. Public virtual schools.
21 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
22 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
23 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
24
Req. No. 17146 Page 2

1 decl ared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
2 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
